body:
**Description**
Halo Text position doesn't match with actual text if paint.TextAlign property different than SKTextAlign.Left

I think the reason is that paint.TextAlign property not been included in the paint.GetTextPath() method.

**Code**

 SKPaint paint = new SKPaint();
paint.TextAlign = SKTextAlign.Center;
// Draw Halo
canvas.DrawPath(paint.GetTextPath("Test Text", 0, 0), haloPaint);
// Draw text
canvas.DrawText("Test Text", 0, 0, paint);


Attached a screenshot of red text with blue halo underneath (using above code), the halo was off because the text Align is Center, but Halo seems still using TextAlign.Left

**Actual Behavior**

  
![Halo offset issue](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/63121477/87454665-e8059600-c5c9-11ea-8426-81ec935e470e.png)

**Basic Information**

- Version with issue:  2.80.1
- Last known good version:  1.68.3
- IDE:  Visual Studio
- Platform Target Frameworks:  tested in Windows, but I believe applies to all platforms
